folder: Spring Street & Greenwich Street, Manhattan, NY
text: (1) 315-311 Spring Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of Greenwich Street. Three old houses which will be demolished prior to 1910 to make way for the Cornell & Underhill warehouse, 309-317 Spring Street and 515-521 Greenwich Street. About 1908. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.  (2) The same, another view. About 1908. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.  (3) The same, from a different angle. About 1900. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Greenwich Street & Spring Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Greenwich Street, east side, at Spring Street; Nos. 501-513 Greenwich Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Spring Street, are frame houses with brick fronts; Ninth Ave., Elevated on Greenwich Street, obstructing the view.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

(2)
The same, showing a rear view of Nos. 505-509 Greenwich Street, south of the S.E. corner of Spring Street. No 507 is a 4-story building.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
